    <item>
      <title>02. Features</title>
      <link>https://elecbrandy.github.io/freshpink/posts/post-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 03 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://elecbrandy.github.io/freshpink/posts/post-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;features&#34;&gt;Features&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;image-area&#34;&gt;Image Area&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This theme provides an image area feature. You can insert a wide image area of your choice at the top of your &lt;code&gt;.md&lt;/code&gt; file according to the tomel format: FEATURED_IMAGE = “ ”`.Insert a nice image that represents your post.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;toc&#34;&gt;TOC&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This theme has a TOC. It&amp;rsquo;s on the left side of the body, and by default, it&amp;rsquo;s transparent so it doesn&amp;rsquo;t get in the way of reading the post. When you hover over it, it actually turns into an actionable text. As for the &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;h1&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; tag, it&amp;rsquo;s considered a heading tag and can be hard to recognize to prevent abuse! Similar to hugo&amp;rsquo;s tendency.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
